This is because background-colors for these components are hardcoded while the text color is not. 

It seems like application css rules for both of these components are the culprit:
```css
.category_page_header_filter_box {
	background-color: #cfcfcd;
	border-bottom: 1px solid darker(#cfcfcd);
}
/* and */
.application-details-infobar {
	background-color: #d3d7cf;
	color: @theme_fg_color;
	border-color: darker(#d3d7cf);
	border-style: solid;
	border-width: 1px;
	padding: 12px;
	text-shadow: none;
}
```

The fix for both of these could be something like:
```css
.category_page_header_filter_box {
	background-color: lighter(@theme_bg_color);
	border-bottom: 1px solid darker(@theme_bg_color);
}


.application-details-infobar {
	background-color: lighter(@theme_bg_color);
	color: @theme_fg_color;
	border-color: darker(@theme_bg_color);
	border-style: solid;
	border-width: 1px;
	padding: 12px;
	text-shadow: none;
}
```

